properties.Name: DunBradstreetFinancialStatement
properties.Description:
The Financial section includes balance sheets, income statements and management estimates or projections when available. If provided, up to three years of comparative summaries may be displayed here. This financial data can help you to assess the following:

A company's ability to meet short term debt by comparing all liquid assets to current liabilities, or all liquid assets plus inventory to current debt.

The amount of capital provided by creditors compared to capital invested by others.

The amount of sales compared to total assets of the company.

The Financial section may also include information on a company's access to additional financial capital, such as accounts, loans and specific banking relationships, as well as bank evaluations (when available) of whether the relationships are satisfactory. Content may not represent the full extent of the firm's banking relationships, nor the primary bank used by the business. Commentary on the absence of financial information may also appear in this section.

Columns.Name: DunsNumber
Columns.Description: Dun & Bradstreet (D&B) provides a D-U-N-S Number, a unique nine digit identification number, for each physical location of your business.

Columns.Name: ReportPurchaseDate
Columns.Description: The purchase date of the report.

Columns.Name: DunBradstreetFinancialStatementTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Dun Bradstreet Financial Statement Type.
